{
  "text": "An important part of the statements above may be reformulated as the claim that the modular functor F Teich is similar in the sense of Definition 5 to a modular functor F Qgrp that is constructed in close analogy to the construction of Reshetikhin-Turaev from the representations of the modular double of U q (sl(2, R)) introduced in [CITATION_1] Fa] and studied in more detail in [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
  "correct_citation": {
